    {
      "id": "1123045658333556867",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2023-06-27T04:22:30.126+04:00",
      "timestampEdited": "2023-06-27T04:24:24.736+04:00",
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Then given a set of files where each file has also a file number, we would create another zkProgram where you provide a file range (from file number 'a' to file number 'b') and a file size range (only files from size 'a' to size 'b'), using a similar recursive strategy than before to prove that we are retrieving ALL files within the range of files that have the requested size range)",
      "author": {
        "id": "1050599472071180389",
        "name": "chrlyz",
        "discriminator": "0000",
        "nickname": "chrlyz",
        "color": "#FA7504",
        "isBot": false,
        "roles": [
